                        <summary>nakṣatra kaṣṭāvalī, an astrological treatise. Anonymous; undated composition; copied 1871, possibly Ambikapur, Chhattisgarh</summary>
                        <textLang mainLang="sa" otherLangs="hi">Sanskrit with Hindi in explicit.</textLang>
                        <msItem xml:id="Alpha_113">
                            <locus>Folio 1; 1A-2B</locus>
                            
                            <title type="main" key="Alpha_113">nakṣatra kaṣṭāvalī</title>
                            
                            <incipit> <locus>1A</locus>
                                <!-- transcript -->
                                pasamānvitaiḥ lāpasī laḍukam śreṣṭhaṃ suhālī tatra dāpayet |
                                bahubhakti samāyuktam aṣṭamāsam mucyate || 14 ||
                                jyeṣṭhāyāṃ vyādhitasyāpi sarvāṅge vedanā bhavet na mantraṃ nauṣadhaṃ tatra meṣaṃ tatra pradāpayet |
                                brahmarājñānasadoṣeṇa saptatrignāsa jīvati || 15 ||
                            </incipit>
                            
                            <explicit><locus>2B</locus>
                                <!-- transcript -->
                                cauthe pa o | to ghaṇā dukhabhogī chuṭai 4 | śu o 15|01 to veganī kahai 1 dūje pa|0|di-4 bhogī chute 2 tīje pa|0|di|4 maisa mādha hoi 3
                                cauthe 5 to vega sūro hai 4 sa |15| todi 8 anai 11 mai chuṭai 1 dūje 5 dina 8 maisātā hai 2 tīje 5 todi 1 bhogavai 3 cau 5 todi 5 mai samādhai hai 4 iti kastāvalī samāptam |
                                <note>Hindi language attribution added by AP based on explicit text. Notation of numerical figures probably incorrect, due to non-standard transliteration in source file.</note>
                            </explicit>
                            
                            <colophon> <locus>2B</locus>
                                <!-- transcript -->
                                likhitai sā devamuni saṃvat 1928 miti māgha kṛṣṇa 7 ambakānagara madhye śubham |
                            </colophon>
                            
